  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Having re-launched <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/games/splitgate-2">Splitgate 2</a> as <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/after-more-than-one-controversy-layoffs-and-a-lengthy-beta-period-splitgate-2-is-set-to-return-next-month">Spligate: Arena Reloaded</a> late last year, 1047 Games have now kicked off early work on a new <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/best-fps-games">shooter</a>. Details are scarce aside from the fact you'll be able to move around in it and that 1047 CEO Ian Proulx reckons it should appeal to fans of <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/games/titanfall">Titanfall</a> and Call of Duty Blops 3. Oh, and that you can sign-up for to playtest it now.</p>
<!--more-->

<figure>
<p>
